        <abstract>
            <p>Cites cases of difference in coloration between the sexes of some species of Crustacea, annelids, and spiders.</p>
            <p>Discusses dimorphic plants and self-sterility.</p>
            <p>Outlines some experiments involving the crossing of different species of orchids.</p> 
<p>Encloses extract from Carl Claus, <hi rend="italic">Die freilebenden Copepoden</hi> [1863].</p> 
        </abstract>
